forgot about the ADCs. Imagine having a huge ban list for one match with all of these guys on it.

Have played 600+ games on ARAM.  Knowing what it stands for is irrelevant to the post I made.

ARAM isn't completely random to begin with, so your point is moot.  Reroll system does nothing to mitigate the ARAM only accounts that fester that game mode.  Reroll and bans are nothing alike.  Reroll is for the individual player and why would they get rid of an OP champ on ARAM?  They wouldn't unless they don't like them (which is rare).  Bans are for players to remove champs from the opposing team to use in the game.

The champs below are a quick and small guide of OP champs on ARAM, which could get banned if a system (like Draft Mode) was in place (and should be).
{{champion:22}}  {{champion:74}}  {{champion:222}}  {{champion:119}}  {{champion:81}} 
{{champion:99}}  {{champion:16}}  {{champion:30}}  {{champion:17}}  {{champion:45}}

League will avoid this like the plague, because it means its pros will need to have much deeper champion pools then they do right now. since this game is much less about team comp and individuals get to make bigger plays in league, target bans would be far more common then they are in Dota. 

Imagine watching top laners deal with 7-9 meta picks banned out 

they wouldn't know what do with themselves. {{champion:32}}
